=== TASK ===
# Inquiry Confirmation

## Overview
Develop a polished Inquiry Confirmation page that appears after a guest submits an inquiry. This page presents a concise summary of the inquiry, communicates the expected concierge response time, outlines next steps (including how payment will be handled), and provides navigational CTAs to view other inquiries or return to exploration. The page should integrate smoothly with the existing Inquiry Submission & Management system, reflecting the lifecycle statuses (New, Contacted, Deposit Paid, Confirmed, etc.) and aligning with the Roam Resort brand’s premium, editorial UI. All data handling must be robust to null/undefined values and guarded against common runtime errors.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A post-submission Confirmation view for an inquiry, focusing on conveying a successful submission, a succinct inquiry summary, the concierge’s expected response time, and concrete next steps including how payment will be handled.

Goals:
- Reinforce confidence and clarity after submission.
- Confirm essential details (inquiry reference, stay details, guest count, message snippet).
- Set expectations for concierge response time and the payment flow (manual Stripe Connect payment when requested by concierge).
- Provide quick navigation to “View My Inquiries” (profile) and “Return to Destinations.”
- Trigger or reflect a backend event to store the inquiry with metadata and to track status through its lifecycle.

Connected features:
- Inquiry Submission & Management: Guest-facing submission, admin/host-facing management, metadata, attachments, and lifecycle tracking.
- Email confirmation: System should flag or indicate that an email confirmation was sent with a reference to the in-platform inquiry.

UI elements and how they need to look:
- Confirmation header: Large, editorial headline with the inquiry reference number.
- Inquiry Summary Card: Key details - dates, destination, guests, room/type if applicable, and a short message snippet.
- Next Steps Section: 
  - "Expected Concierge Response Time" with a clearly stated SLA (e.g., within 24–48 hours) and any caveats.
  - "Payment Flow" subsection describing payment expectations, manual steps, and how and when Stripe Connect will be used (if applicable).
  - Contact support options and links (email, help center).
- Email Confirmation Notice: A small section or badge indicating that a confirmation email has been sent; provide a link to re-send (optional) if supported.
- CTAs:
  - Primary: View My Inquiries (links to guest profile’s inquiries tab)
  - Secondary: Return to Destinations (navigates back to destinations page)
- Attachments/Metadata: If present, show a compact summary of any file attachments that were included with the inquiry (icon + filename, size) or a note if attachments exist; otherwise omit.
- Visual guidance: Clean, generous spacing with editorial blocks; use muted but warm backgrounds; ensure emphasis on the reference number and next steps.

Integration details:
- Data must reflect the latest persisted inquiry data from the submission API (ideally via a responsive fetch to the inquiry detail endpoint if needed to populate after submission).
- Ensure that any user-triggered navigation from this page respects authentication and proper routing guards.
- Ensure the page handles absence of certain data gracefully (e.g., no attachments, no message snippet, unknown SLA) by providing safe defaults.

## Components to Build
- InquiryConfirmationPage
  - Props/state: inquiryId, userContext (guest), loadedData (optional), flags for attachment presence
  - Sub-components:
    - ConfirmationHeader
      - Displays: "Inquiry Confirmed" + reference number
    - InquirySummaryCard
      - Displays: destination, dates, guests, snippet
      - Guard for missing fields
    - NextStepsPanel
      - Displays: Concierge response SLA, payment flow details, support links
    - EmailConfirmationBadge
      - Displays status about email confirmation; optional link to re-send
    - ActionsBar
      - ViewMyInquiriesButton
      - ReturnToDestinationsButton
  - Data handling: Use data ?? [] guarded rendering; always validate array/objects before mapping or rendering lists
- AttachmentRow (optional)
  - Displays: file icon, name, size; only if attachments exist
- LoadingSkeletons (optional)
  - For improved UX while data loads

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Routing & Page
  - Route: /inquiries/confirmation/:inquiryId (or similar) with parameterized ID
  - Redirects and guards if user not authenticated
- UI Components
  - Card components with soft shadows, rounded corners (8–12px), light borders
  - Typography: Follow design system with Playfair Display (Headlines) and Inter/Lato for UI/body
  - Buttons: Bronze-gold fill (#A97C50) with subtle shadow; hover states brighten/darken
  - Typography treatments: Section labels uppercase, with ample spacing
- State Management
  - useState<T[]>([]) pattern for any array state (e.g., attachments)
  - useEffect calls to fetch inquiry data using given inquiryId
  - Guard all array/map calls: (attachments ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(attachments) ? attachments.map(...) : []
- Data Handling & Safety
  - Initialize all arrays with defaults and provide fallback strings for missing fields
  - Use optional chaining when accessing nested data
  - Ensure no runtime errors if data is null/undefined
- Accessibility
  - Semantic HTML, ARIA labels for interactive elements
  - Keyboard navigable CTAs
  - Color contrast compliance with the provided palette
- Performance
  - Minimal re-renders; memoization where appropriate; lazy-load any optional sections if data is heavy

### Backend
- APIs
  - GET /inquiries/:inquiryId to fetch detail (reference, summary fields, status, attachments, eta)
  - POST /inquiries to submit a new inquiry (already existing in flow)
  - PATCH /inquiries/:inquiryId to update status or notes (for admin/host)
- Database Tables (Core schema)
  - inquiries
    - id (UUID)
    - user_id (FK to users)
    - destination_id (FK to destinations)
    - start_date, end_date
    - guests
    - message (text)
    - reference (string)
    - status (enum: New, Contacted, DepositPaid, Confirmed, Closed)
    - attachments (JSONB) -> array of { id, filename, mimeType, url, size }
    - created_at, updated_at
    - payment_required (boolean)
    - payment_state (enum: Pending, Completed, Failed, NotRequired)
  - inquiries_metadata (optional for extensibility)
- Validation
  - Ensure required fields on submission; safe defaults on retrieval
  - Ensure attachments are sanitized and do not contain harmful content
- Security
  - Ensure endpoints validate user authentication and authorization to view specific inquiries
  - Admin endpoints restricted to Concierge role
- Email/Notifications
  - Trigger email confirmation on submission (existing flow)
  - Optional: push notification to guest with reference

### Integration
- Data flow:
  - After submission, frontend fetches inquiry detail using inquiryId to render confirmation
  - If necessary, fetch along with attachments; guard null results
  - Ensure consistency between submission payload and detail view
- State synchronization:
  - If the inquiry status changes in the admin panel, consider a real-time or polling approach for the confirmation page to reflect updated status (optional)

## User Experience Flow
1. Guest submits an inquiry via the Stay Inquiry form
2. System saves inquiry with metadata, attachments, and a generated reference
3. User is navigated to /inquiries/confirmation/:inquiryId
4. Page loads: shows Confirmation Header with reference, Inquiry Summary Card (destination, dates, guests, snippet), Next Steps (response time, payment flow), Email Confirmation badge, and CTAs
5. User can click:
   - View My Inquiries -> navigates to guest profile inquiries tab
   - Return to Destinations -> navigates to destinations landing
6. If email confirmation was sent, the badge confirms; otherwise, a subtle prompt may offer to re-send
7. Admin/Concierge side updates status as needed; frontend should reflect status if data updates (optional real-time)

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: 
- inquiries
  - id: UUID
  - user_id: UUID
  - destination_id: UUID
  - start_date: date
  - end_date: date
  - guests: integer
  - message: text
  - reference: string
  - status: enum ('New','Contacted','DepositPaid','Confirmed','Closed')
  - attachments: JSONB (array of { id, filename, mimeType, url, size })
  - created_at: timestamp
  - updated_at: timestamp
  - payment_required: boolean
  - payment_state: enum ('Pending','Completed','Failed','NotRequired')
- destinations (existing)
  - id, name, location, etc.
- users (existing)
  - id, email, name, etc.

API Endpoints:
- GET /inquiries/:inquiryId
  - Response: { id, reference, destination: {id,name}, start_date, end_date, guests, messageSnippet, status, attachments: [{filename,url,mimeType,size, id}], payment_required, payment_state, created_at, updated_at, email_confirmed }
- PATCH /inquiries/:inquiryId
  - Body: { status?: string, internalNotes?: string }
- GET /inquiries?userId=... (optional, for in-page consistency)
- POST /inquiries (existing)

Security:
- Authenticate guest user for GET/inquiries/:inquiryId
- Admin/Concierge endpoints protected by role (admin/concierge)
- JWT or session-based auth as per project standard

Validation:
- Ensure inquiryId param is a valid UUID
- Validate response shapes: Array.isArray(attachments) ? attachments : []
- Use data ?? [] patterns on all array results
- Use destructuring with defaults for API responses: const { attachments = [], reference = '', destination = {}, message = '', status = 'New' } = response ?? {}

Optional: real-time updates via WebSocket or long-polling for status changes (if the platform supports)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Inquiry Confirmation page renders with a valid reference, destination, dates, guest count, and message snippet; all fields gracefully degrade if data is missing
- [ ] No runtime errors when any field is null/undefined; all arrays guarded: (attachments ?? []).map(...)
- [ ] Buttons function correctly: View My Inquiries navigates to guest profile; Return to Destinations navigates home or destinations page
- [ ] Email confirmation badge displays correctly when email_confirmed is true
- [ ] Payment flow description clearly communicates manual Stripe Connect steps and when they occur
- [ ] Data fetching uses safe defaults: const inquiry = response?.data ?? {}; const attachments = Array.isArray(inquiry.attachments) ? inquiry.attachments : []
- [ ] Admin/concierge flow remains compatible with lifecycle statuses and supports updating status and internal notes (for future extension)

